<font color="#FF0000">CRAZY DAYS OF SUMMER</font><br>
<tt>Sat Nov 22 21:09:48 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I remember the day that we decided to dig Charlie out of his tunneled 37mm sites in the north.  We all massed just short of the fence in Northern Laos.  The boys continued to hang loose while the main joined up.  Nobody knew what to expect.  An F-4 showed carrying only one weapon and internal 20 mic mic.  That weapon was on centerline and damn near the full length of the aircraft.  He was barely able to hold angels 15 and was in and out of min burner.  He was worried as hell about running out of fuel.  A tanker showed to follow the group in to make sure they had the gas to get out.<br><br>
Crazy bunch all at 340 kts 15k and flying through northern Laos on a nice clear day.<br><br>
Did I forget to mention the weapon was a propane bomb a.k.a. fuel bomb?  The one we never dropped.<br><br>
Well the bomb was dropped on target.  Created a ground zero.  Burns air so fast a vacuum is created.  Below or above the ground got your guts sucked out through your asshole.  Shortly after that they were looking for volunteer gunners.<br><br>
Crazy days of summer<br>

<p><code>--   (SW) </code><p>


